Stelios Calls for EasyJet to Reduce Number of Aircraft, Sky Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-12T18:42:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/stelios-calls-for-easyjet-to-reduce-number-of-aircraft-sky-says.html
Stelios Haji-Ioannou , the founder of
 EasyJet Plc (EZJ) , wrote to EasyJet Chairman Michael Rake yesterday to
reiterate his call for the airline to reduce the number of
aircraft it owns and return up to 600 million pounds ($956
million) to shareholders, Sky News  reported , citing the letter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 